    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.01892.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Bowling Green</name> 
                    <date when="1867-02-24"><choice>
                                <orig>Febry</orig>
                                <reg>February</reg>
                            </choice> 24th</date>
                    <date when="1867-02-24">1867<ptr target="loc.01892_n1"/></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My Dear Friend</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I was thinking <choice>
                    <orig>to day</orig>
                    <reg>today</reg>
                </choice> whether I had answered your last letter or not but I am going to write you
                    anyhow<space dim="horizontal" extent="5 letters"/>The most news at present is
                about the high water of which we have plenty &amp; to spare even to the big folks at
                Washington if they need any<space dim="horizontal" extent="3 letters"/> The weather
                is warm and spring is fairly advanced people are plowing &amp; wheat looks first
                although I am not interested in agriculture I am glad to see things <pb
                    xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.01892.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/> thriving. I have
                been engaged in the oil business the past year but I find it a losing <unclear
                    reason="illegible" resp="#cn" cert="medium">game</unclear> and now I am out of
                employment and floating around &amp; its hard to tell when I shall turn up &amp;
                whether it will be up side down or right side up If I had known in time I might
                possibly have got the nomination for Governor of this
                state<!--Shively's note: Kentucky--> but ex Gov. Helm<ptr target="loc.01892_n2"/>
                has beat me. That you know would have been better than lying around idle now I must
                look for something else for a living. I might steal if I knew enough but I have not
                even the first <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc.01892.003_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
                rudiments of the profession and then it leads to unpleasant things when one gets
                caught at it I think of going to Nashville this week and can see if I can get work
                there something from blacking boots down to sweeping crossings I think if Gov
                    Brownlow<ptr target="n0749"/> knew me he would not hesitate to give me a good
                berth in Tennessee but being of a modest disposition of course I cannot call his
                attention to my many merits</p>
            <p>Now you must not think I am egotistical at all for I am not I am only telling you
                what most every one knows as <hi rend="underline">true</hi> anything <unclear
                    reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#kk">about me</unclear>
                <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc.01892.004_large.jpg" type="verso"/> It's Sunday
                evening I'm sitting alone sad &amp; lonely, no dog to love no one to talk with Time
                hangs heavily and yet they say time flies <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#cn"
                    cert="medium">fleetly</unclear>, Ah it may be I have seen the time when minutes
                were hours &#38; hours days but that is gone yes <choice>
                    <sic>its</sic>
                    <corr>it's</corr>
                </choice> near two years since those scenes were past And May God in his mercy
                deliver us from the curse of war where so many meet their death or are thrown back
                upon the world a poor miserable cripple a <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium"
                    resp="#cn">invalid</unclear> to themselves and of no benefit to country or
                friends</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>I remain affectionately</salute>
                <salute>your friend</salute>
                <signed><hi rend="underline">Anson Rider <choice>
                            <abbr>Junr</abbr>
                            <expan>Junior</expan>
                        </choice></hi></signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
                <p>If<ptr target="loc.01892_n3"/> you direct to this place I shall get your answer even if I am not here</p>
                <signed>Anson</signed> 
            </postscript>
